@startuml network-scenario-3-onsite
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 8

title **Scenario 3 — Onsite (Corporate WiFi / Ethernet, no VPN)**

left to right direction

node "MacBook" as MB {
  [detect-network.sh] as DET
  [Proxydetox\n:3128] as PD
  [Claude CLI] as CLI
  [OpenCode\n(Copilot provider)] as OC
}

rectangle "BMW Corporate Network (Onsite)" as CN {
  [PAC Server\nmuc.proxy-pac.\nbmwgroup.net] as PAC
  [Central Proxy\n(Squid/BlueCoat)] as CP
  [Firewall\n(URL category filter)] as FW #FFCDD2
}

cloud "Internet" as INET {
  [api.anthropic.com] as AN
  [api.github.com] as GH
}

' Detection
DET -[#green]-> PAC : 1. DNS resolves ✓\n→ INSIDE_CN=true

' Claude flow (blocked)
CLI -[#green,bold]-> PD : 2. https_proxy=:3128
PD -[#green,bold]-> CP : 3. CONNECT :443
CP -[#green,bold]-> FW : 4. URL category check
FW -[#red,bold]-> AN : **BLOCKED (403)**\nCategory: "AI/ML APIs"\n(not approved)

' OpenCode flow (works)
OC -[#green,bold]-> PD
FW -[#green,bold]-> GH : **ALLOWED** ✓\nCategory: "Dev Tools"

note bottom of MB
  **INSIDE_CN = true** (direct corporate DNS)
  **Network detection passes** — proxy works fine.
  **Same firewall policy as VPN** — api.anthropic.com
  is blocked by URL category filter (AI/ML).
  api.github.com passes (Developer Tools).

  **Result: Claude BLOCKED. Use OpenCode + Copilot instead.**
  (Copilot routes through api.github.com which is allowed)
end note

@enduml
